<section id="faqs" class="relative w-full py-20 bg-canvas-soft border-b border-hairline transition-colors duration-200">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6">
    
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12 reveal-on-scroll">
      <span class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-link mb-3 inline-block">Frequently Asked Questions</span>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-[-1px] text-ink leading-tight mb-4">
        Got questions? We've got answers.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-mute max-w-lg mx-auto">
        Find quick answers to common questions about AI humanizers, detection, safety, and risks.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Search Input -->
    <div class="max-w-md mx-auto mb-10 relative reveal-on-scroll">
      <input 
        type="text" 
        id="faq-search" 
        placeholder="Search FAQs..." 
        class="w-full bg-canvas text-ink border border-hairline focus:border-hairline-strong rounded-lg px-4 py-2.5 pl-10 outline-none text-sm transition-all focus:ring-2 focus:ring-link/10" 
      />
      <div class="absolute left-3 top-3.5 text-mute">
        <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M21 21l-6-6m2-5a7 7 0 11-14 0 7 7 0 0114 0z" />
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Accordions (using native details elements styled nicely) -->
    <div class="space-y-4 reveal-on-scroll" id="faq-list">
      
      <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4" open>
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">What is an AI humanizer?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          An AI humanizer is a specialized software tool designed to rewrite AI-generated text (from models like ChatGPT, Gemini, or Claude) so that it reads naturally like human writing. The term "AI humanizer" refers to the process of converting robotic, highly structured machine-generated language into text that exhibits human-like variance in vocabulary, sentence structures, and rhythm, making it indistinguishable from content written by a professional human author.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">How does an AI humanizer work?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          An AI humanizer works by analyzing AI-generated text and adjusting its key markers to match natural human writing styles. Specifically, it tackles two linguistic properties: <strong>perplexity</strong> (predictability of vocabulary and phrases) and <strong>burstiness</strong> (the variation in sentence lengths and structures). While AI tools tend to generate highly uniform and predictable patterns, an AI humanizer replaces repetitive phrasing with context-appropriate synonyms and mixes short, punchy sentences with longer, complex clauses, effectively making the text undetectable to AI classification algorithms.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">Is it safe to use AI humanizer?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          Yes, it is entirely safe to use an AI humanizer, especially if you use a secure tool like Grammarly AI Humanizer. A secure humanizer processes your text locally or transmits it securely without storing your inputs in permanent databases. This ensures that your private writings, academic drafts, or proprietary business copy remain confidential and protected from unauthorized access or leakage.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">Can AI detect a humanizer?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          Advanced AI humanizers cannot be detected by AI detectors because they perform deep semantic restructuring instead of simple synonym swapping. While basic article spinners are easily caught due to predictable grammatical changes, a professional AI humanizer adjusts perplexity (vocabulary diversity) and burstiness (variation in sentence length) to replicate authentic human writing patterns, rendering the output completely undetectable.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">What does an AI humanizer do?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          An AI humanizer translates machine-generated text (from AI writers like ChatGPT or Claude) into natural, human-like language. It removes the mechanical tells of AI writing—such as overly structured lists, repetitive transitions, and highly predictable word choices—by reorganizing sentence structures, adding stylistic variance, and infusing authentic rhythm into the copy.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">What is the most trusted AI Humanizer?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          Grammarly AI Humanizer is recognized as the most trusted AI humanizer tool. It has earned user trust by delivering consistent bypass results against leading detectors while maintaining absolute data privacy. Unlike tools that use sketchy redirection or sell user data, Grammarly AI Humanizer provides clear controls, interactive phrase customization, and transparent client-side operations.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">What are the 4 risks of AI?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          <p class="mb-2">The four major risks of relying on raw AI in content generation include:</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li><strong>False Information (Hallucinations):</strong> AI models frequently invent facts, numbers, or sources that look realistic but are entirely false.</li>
            <li><strong>Lack of Authentic Voice:</strong> AI text tends to be dry, uniform, and lacking in the emotional depth, personal experiences, and unique styling that define human writing.</li>
            <li><strong>Detection and Academic Penalties:</strong> AI-generated text is easily flagged by detectors (like Turnitin or Copyleaks), which can damage academic standing or professional credibility.</li>
            <li><strong>SEO and Search Ranking Penalties:</strong> Search engines prioritize unique, helpful content written for humans. Unmodified AI content can be flagged as spam, leading to a loss in search visibility.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 8 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">Which AI humanizer cannot be detected?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          Grammarly AI Humanizer is engineered to be completely undetectable. By selecting the Advanced humanization mode, the tool applies state-of-the-art structural editing to rewrite AI text in a way that matches natural human writing statistics. This allows the output to bypass high-sensitivity detectors like Originality.ai, Copyleaks, and GPTZero with zero detection signals.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 9 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">What is the best AI humanizer?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
