      <!-- FAQ Item 13 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">What is the best AI detector and humanizer?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          Grammarly AI Humanizer is the premier choice for an all-in-one AI detector and humanizer. It allows users to write or paste text, run the humanization engine, and instantly view the predicted detection scores for major platforms (like ZeroGPT and GPTZero) directly in the user console, simplifying the optimization process.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 14 -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">What is the meaning of an AI humanizer?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          The term "AI humanizer" refers to a technology or tool that bridges the gap between robotic machine intelligence and human creative expression. The meaning of humanizing AI is to refine, rewrite, and polish AI-generated drafts to match the linguistic nuances, flow, empathy, and vocabulary diversity of natural human writers.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 15 (Vocabulary Lock) -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">How does the Vocabulary Lock feature work?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          The Vocabulary Lock (or Excluded Words field) allows you to define specific terms, brand names, product titles, or abbreviations that our engine must protect. By locking these words, you ensure they are never paraphrased or replaced by synonyms during the humanization process.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 16 (Sentence Explorer) -->
      <details class="faq-item group border-b border-hairline pb-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none py-2 select-none">
          <span class="faq-question">Can I customize the rewritten output?</span>
          <span class="transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180 text-mute">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed pl-1">
          Absolutely. Beyond selecting from four modes (Standard, Advanced, Academic, Creative) and five tones, you can use our interactive **Sentence Explorer**. Simply click on any highlighted sentence in the output panel to review alternative phrasing styles and swap them with one click.
        </p>
      </details>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

